  <section class="moto-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="moto-container">
      <div class="moto-section-header">
        <h2 class="moto-section-title">Motorola Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="moto-section-subtitle">Common questions about Motorola repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="moto-faq-list">
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>How much does Motorola screen repair cost in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Motorola repair costs vary by model — Moto G and E series screens are generally the most accessible in the lineup, while Edge flagships and Razr foldables cost more due to premium OLED panels and complex disassembly. Contact us or use our online quote tool for a free upfront price on your specific model.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Motorola Razr foldable phones in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Yes — we're one of the few Winnipeg repair shops with experience servicing Motorola Razr foldables including the inner foldable screen, outer display, hinge mechanism, and flex cable assembly. Contact us before visiting to confirm parts availability for your specific Razr model and get an accurate quote.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does Motorola repair take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Most Motorola Moto G and Edge screen and battery repairs are completed same-day in 1–2 hours at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. Razr foldable repairs take longer due to complexity, and parts for some Razr models may require a short sourcing window — we'll give you an estimated time when you contact us.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Is it worth repairing my Moto G or Moto E in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">In most cases yes — Moto G and E series phones are well-built devices and screen or battery repairs are typically straightforward. We provide a free diagnostic and upfront quote so you can make an informed decision before committing to any repair.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you stock Motorola parts in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">We stock common parts for all current Moto G and Edge series models for same-day repairs. Razr foldable parts and less common models may require a short sourcing window of 1–3 business days — contact us with your specific model to confirm availability before visiting.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Motorola Edge screens in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Yes — we replace OLED screens on all Motorola Edge models including Edge 30, 40, and 50 series at our Winnipeg location. Edge Pro and Ultra models use curved OLED displays that require model-specific panels — we use quality matched parts to maintain the original display quality after repair.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix a Motorola that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Yes — a non-responsive Motorola is often caused by a depleted battery, a failed display connection, or a software boot issue. We run free diagnostics to identify the root cause before recommending any repair so you know exactly what the problem is before spending anything.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Motorola charging ports in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Yes — we repair USB-C charging ports on all Motorola models at our Winnipeg location. We always clean the port first before recommending replacement since debris is a common cause of Moto G and Moto E charging issues — most charging port repairs are completed same-day.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you offer a warranty on Motorola repairs?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Yes — screen repairs carry a 30-day to lifetime warranty depending on part tier. Battery replacements include a 90-day warranty, and most other repairs carry a lifetime warranty on parts and labour across the full Motorola lineup.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="moto-faq-item">
          <summary class="moto-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Motorola phones in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="moto-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="moto-faq-answer">Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts Motorola repairs Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. For Razr foldables or less common Edge models, calling ahead helps us confirm parts availability before your visit.</p>
